export const lookup = {
  "About Me!": {
    ispanel: true,
    type: "textarea",

    isrc: "about.png",
    text_index: 0,

  "Linked-in": {
    ispanel: false,
    type: "link",

    isrc: "linkedin.png",
  },
  Github: {
    ispanel: false,

    isrc: "github.png",

  "how it all started": {
    ispanel: false,
    type: "link",

    isrc: "howitallstarted.png",
  },
  Notepad: {
    ispanel: true,
    type: "textarea",
    src: "",
    isrc: "note.png",
    text_index: 1,
  },
  "celery man": {
    ispanel: true,
    type: "iframe",
    src: "https://www.youtube.com/embed/maAFcEU6atk",
    isrc: "celeryman.png",
  },
  monkey: {
    ispanel: true,
    type: "img",
    src: "monkey.jpeg",
    isrc: "monkey.png",
  },

export const text_entries = [
  "Welcome to my site!" +
    "\r\n" +
    "\r\n" +
    "Please poke around! You can see the code for my website at" +
    "\r\n" +
    "\r\n" +
    "github[dot]com/balbphegor/98-in-react" +
    "\r\n" +
    "\r\n" +
    "or click the Github icon in the desktop! You can find my other projects there as well!" +
    "\r\n" +
    "\r\n" +
    "Have any suggestions/concerns about the site? Contact me on Linkedin! at linkedin[dot]com/in/calvin-lin-b25618143/ or click the Linkedin icon! " +
    "\r\n" +
    "\r\n" +
    "My name is Calvin Lin and I like golf, running, beer and all possible combinations of the three. I am bad at golf at a -30 handicap, moderately okay at running and great at drinking beer." +
    "\r\n" +
    "\r\n" +
    "I graduated the University of Toronto in 2021 (delayed because of COVID) in Mathematics. Check out my blog by clicking the blog icon to read about my thoughts and experiences not limited to my schooling!" +
    "\r\n" +
    "\r\n" +
    "Everyone in my family is artistically inclined to some degree and I like think that my prowress with CSS is my personal artistic expression. I strive for good and organized CSS. (No bootstrap!)" +
    "\r\n" +
    "\r\n" +
    "I chose to stylize my website theme according to the Windows 98 theme: the first computer my family could afford after immigrating to Canada." +
    "\r\n" +
    "\r\n" +
    "Released in 1998 (my birth-year) I figured that it would be quite fitting that I modelled my site after the first computer interface I ever laid my hands on.",
  "",
];
